GREATER CHINA DAYBOOK: Foreign Direct Investment Growth Likely Accelerates

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-16T23:38:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/greater-china-daybook-foreign-direct-investment-growth-likely-accelerates.html
Foreign direct investment in  China 
probably increased 36.1 percent on year in April, accelerating
from 32.9 percent in March, according to the median estimate of
three economists surveyed by Bloomberg News.  The Ministry of Commerce is scheduled to hold a press
conference to announce the numbers at 10 a.m. in Beijing today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  